# 11. ４人だから

Miku: Tsukasa! You guys!
Tsukasa: *Gasp*
Tsukasa: Huh? Where are we...? Aboard a ship...?
Tsukasa: We were just doing a show at the Wonder Stage...
Luka: A show?
Miku: What?! You guys all dreamt about doing a show?!
Nene: Huh? Dream? What are you talking about...? We were really just doing a show, and...
Luka: I don't understand.
MEIKO: You all became enveloped in that light and suddenly fell asleep.
Luka: Yes. After that, we decided to carry you all here.
Emu: R-Really...?! Hmmm... Now my head's spinning!
Nene: Mine too... But we somehow managed to get back...
Rui: Yes, it would seem so...
Rui: However, even if we did fall asleep, I doubt that was any ordinary dream.
Tsukasa: Yes, you might be right...
Tsukasa: It felt so real.
Len: Y-Y-Y-You guys!!
Rin: We have super big news!
KAITO: Huh? Rin...?! Len...?!
Len: Oh, you guys are all awake! Thank goodness... We were so worried!
Nene: *Nod* Th-Thanks...
Rui: Still, you two seem very anxious. What was this about big news...?
Rin: Oh, that's right! So, the thing is...
Rin: That tree grew really big all of a sudden!
Tsukasa: The tree...?!
Tsukasa: Wh-Wh...
Tsukasa: What in the world happened?!
Nene: When we saw it earlier, it was a lot smaller... How is this even possible...?
Emu: It's so big...! Bigger than you, Rui!
Robo-Nene: It has grown at a tremendous pace.
Rin: So, Rui, you guys all fell asleep after you touched the black stuff on the tree.
Rin: After that happened, we started inspecting every inch of it!
Len: Yeah, we wanted to see if we could find a way to wake you guys back up!
Len: Then, all the black things suddenly started to glow bright white...
Len: It was so bright that we ended up closing our eyes, but once we could open them back up...
Rui: It had grown this big, yes?
Tsukasa: Wait, that still doesn't explain anything!
Emu: But all the black fragments are gone. Does that mean it's all better now?
KAITO: I don't know if this is the case... But what if the tree used those fragments to grow to this size?
Tsukasa: You mean it used those awful-looking things...?!
Nene: Now that you mention it, MEIKO said that those flecks resembled fragments of feelings... But they weren't exactly the same because they were all black...
Miku: Then, did they make you guys have that dream...?
MEIKO: That's certainly a possibility.
Luka: Come to think of it, what was your dream about exactly...?
Tsukasa: Ah, that's right. We hadn't fully described what happened yet. As for me...
KAITO: So, you all dreamed about your troupe becoming separated...?
Tsukasa: Yes. We'd chosen to go our separate ways and pursue our dreams on our own.
Tsukasa: And for some strange reason, we couldn't really remember anything about SEKAI or any of you...
Rin: Really...?
Len: But why did it make you have that kind of dream...?
KAITO: ...
KAITO: I have no proof of this...
KAITO: But those fragments may've shown you that dream because of the feelings that lingered within all of you...
Tsukasa: Feelings that lingered within all of us...?
KAITO: The fear that you'd become separated and never see each other again. You've all considered the possibility before, no?
Nene: Oh...
KAITO: As we all know, that never came to pass. But...
KAITO: It doesn't seem too farfetched to think that all the doubts, worries and pain you'd been harboring managed to manifest in SEKAI right at that moment.
KAITO: So, I have a feeling that you saw that dream because you had those feelings lingering inside of you...
Rui: In other words, it took all those feelings and showed us a world of “What if?”
Emu: But I thought this was Tsukasa's SEKAI. Why were we able to see that dream?
MEIKO: There's a simple answer to that...
MEIKO: Yes, this is indeed Tsukasa's SEKAI, but you and the others can come and go as you please.
MEIKO: So, it certainly wouldn't surprise me to hear that your feelings are also able to affect this SEKAI.
Nene: D-Does it really work like that...?
KAITO: Again, these are just possibilities. But the fact is that the stronger your feelings are, the greater the impact you'll have on SEKAI.
Tsukasa: Yes, I think I understand now. In layman's terms...
Tsukasa: The pain and conflict we endured long ago has come back to help us grow! Does that sound right...?
Nene: Huh...?! How did you arrive on that...?!
Tsukasa: Hm? I thought that was the obvious conclusion from the start.
Tsukasa: Think about it. Our tree here grew to this tremendous size after absorbing all those black fragments.
Tsukasa: And from the sound of things, those fragments seem to have represented all of our worst doubts and fears. Which means...
Tsukasa: We need to overcome that pain and suffering. No, not just overcome it. We need to turn it into nutrients for growth...!
Len: Hmmm... I sorta get what you're trying to say, but also don't...
Miku: Hehe...☆ But it's a super duper great expression of who you are, Tsukasa♪
Emu: Yeah! It's got this bang-boom-zippity-zoom feel to it☆
Tsukasa: Hah hah hah! I'll take that as a compliment.
Nene: *Sigh* Honestly, you guys are way too positive...
Nene: That being said... I did learn a few things from that dream.
Luka: You learned a few things?
Nene: Yeah. Even though I kept pursuing my dream after we went our separate ways... A lot of things didn't go too well for me on my own.
Nene: So, I realize now just how incredibly important it was for me to stay with you guys and grow together as a troupe.
Rui: I know what you mean. I honestly felt a little relieved when I realized that it was all just a dream...
Rui: As interesting a dream as it was.
Emu: Yeah... When I woke up and saw you guys next to me...
Emu: I started tearing up a little.
Tsukasa: Our dreams mean everything to us. That will never change.
Tsukasa: However, it's nice to have your friends by your side while you're chasing after them...
Tsukasa: Because we make each other stronger!
Tsukasa: I was reminded of just how precious the time we get to spend putting on shows together is.
Tsukasa: I learned that there are certain lessons and experiences we can only have together!
Emu: Yeah...! So, let's keep doing everything we can together☆
KAITO: Hehe. And we'll keep watching over all of you as you try to make your dreams a reality... We'll always be here.
Tsukasa: Yes, we greatly appreciate your support!
Emu: Hey, wanna head back and start practicing for that show?!
Nene: Oh, right... I totally forgot about that.
Rui: Hehe. That dream did sort of make us lose track of time.
Tsukasa: Right. Even though we're all back, I still don't feel like I've fully returned...
Tsukasa: So, why don't we do something to refocus our attention on the task at hand?
Tsukasa: Like our usual chant. It feels like it's been so long...
Rui: Yes, that seems like a nice idea.
Miku: Woohoo☆ Then, we'll join you guys♪
Rin: Yeah! With big smiles☆
Tsukasa: Alright, Emu! You have the honors! Take it away!
Emu: Okay☆
Emu: Everyone! Let's keep trying really hard and doing everything we can together☆
Emu: Ready?! Won-Won-Won-Won...
Everyone: Wonderhoy!
